Read the triage assess skill instructions at {{.WorkflowPath}}/skills/assess.md
and follow them to assess the Jira bug {{.IssueURL}}.

## MCP Server

A Jira MCP server is configured under the name "jira". Use its tools for
all Jira read operations (searching issues, fetching details). The skill
instructions may reference different tool names — use whichever Jira tools
are available from the configured MCP server.

## Output

After completing the assessment, write two output files:

1. **{{.OutputPath}}** — the full triage assessment as an Atlassian Document
   Format (ADF) JSON object. The top-level structure must be:
   ```json
   {
     "type": "doc",
     "version": 1,
     "content": [ ... ]
   }
   ```
   Use proper ADF node types: heading, paragraph, table, bulletList,
   orderedList, codeBlock, rule, etc. Use marks for bold, italic, code,
   and links. Do not include the "On Completion" section.
   Write ONLY the raw JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text.

2. **{{.MetadataPath}}** — a JSON metadata file with this structure:
   ```json
   {
     "recommendation": "<type>",
     "confidence": "<High|Medium|Low>",
     "autoFixLikelihood": <0-100 or null>
   }
   ```
   Where `<type>` is one of: CLOSE, FIX_NOW, AUTO_FIX, BACKLOG,
   NEEDS_INFO, DUPLICATE, ESCALATE, WONT_FIX.
   Set autoFixLikelihood only when recommendation is AUTO_FIX; otherwise set it to null.
